  "description": "Harry Fritiof August Josefson was a chaplain in Hyssna. He was born in Tanum, Gothenburg and Bohuslän on May 22, 1909, the son of railway employee Axel J. and Ida Johansson. He graduated from Uddevalla High School in 1928, became a theological candidate in 1930, passed the practical theological examination in 1934, and was ordained as a minister in the Gothenburg diocese in 1935. He served as a curate in Öckerö, Skepplanda, and Tanum, assistant vicar in Grebbestad, and assistant in Gothenburg diocese (with placement in Sikagen, Denmark), where he also served as the chaplain to Swedish fishermen in Denmark, Norway, England, and Scotland. He was a church assistant in Lysekil in 1942 and a chaplain in Hyssna from 1942 until his death. He was also the chairman of the Hyssna church meeting and a member of the Gothenburg diocese diaconal council."
